text: The Rosey Park Bridge is a historic bridge built in West Virginia. It was built in 1929 and is made out of wood and stone in a old fashioned style. It is approximately 53 metres long and 9 metres wide. The bridge was added to the National Register of Historic Places in the year 2002. == References == Category:Bridges in the United States Category:National Register of Historic Places
